---
// Shared payload for the panel-UX samples: the Traction Budget explained in
// three ADDITIVE tiers. Tier 1 is always shown; deeper tiers append below it.
import Math from './Math.astro';
---

<div class="mathtiers">
  <!-- ── TIER 1 — always visible ── -->
  <div class="tier tier-1">
    <div class="tier-tag tier-tag-1">Tier 1 · The idea</div>
    <p class="tier-p">
      One tyre has <strong>one grip budget</strong>, shared between going/slowing
      (longitudinal) and turning (lateral). Treat the limit as the same in every
      direction — a circle of radius <Math expr={String.raw`\mu g`} />. Demands add as a vector:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`\left(\tfrac{F_x}{F_{\max}}\right)^2 + \left(\tfrac{F_y}{F_{\max}}\right)^2 \le 1`} />
    <p class="tier-p">
      So 70% brake + 70% lean is fine: <Math expr={String.raw`0.7^2 + 0.7^2 = 0.98 \le 1`} />.
      Cross the circle and you've asked for more grip than exists.
    </p>
  </div>

  <button class="tier-btn btn-2" data-reveal="2">＋ Go deeper — real tyre behaviour</button>

  <!-- ── TIER 2 — appended ── -->
  <div class="tier tier-2" hidden>
    <div class="tier-tag tier-tag-2">Tier 2 · Real tyre behaviour <span class="kept">(Tier 1 still holds)</span></div>
    <p class="tier-p">
      The circle is really an <strong>ellipse</strong> — peak grip differs longitudinally
      vs laterally, so:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`\left(\tfrac{F_x}{F_{x,\max}}\right)^2 + \left(\tfrac{F_y}{F_{y,\max}}\right)^2 \le 1`} />
    <p class="tier-p">
      And <strong>grip is load-sensitive</strong>: the friction coefficient falls as
      vertical load rises, so the budget itself breathes with weight transfer:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`\mu(F_z) = \mu_0 - k\,F_z, \qquad k > 0`} />
    <p class="tier-p">
      A leaned tyre also makes lateral force from <strong>camber thrust</strong>, not just
      slip — so lean angle <Math expr={String.raw`\gamma`} /> contributes directly:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`F_y \approx C_\alpha\,\alpha + C_\gamma\,\gamma`} />
  </div>

  <button class="tier-btn btn-3" data-reveal="3" hidden>＋ What's actually happening</button>

  <!-- ── TIER 3 — appended ── -->
  <div class="tier tier-3" hidden>
    <div class="tier-tag tier-tag-3">Tier 3 · What's actually happening <span class="kept">(both tiers still hold)</span></div>
    <p class="tier-p">
      Tyre force is a nonlinear function of slip ratio <Math expr={String.raw`\kappa`} /> and slip
      angle <Math expr={String.raw`\alpha`} />, captured by Pacejka's Magic Formula:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`F = D\,\sin\!\Big(C\arctan\!\big(Bs - E(Bs - \arctan Bs)\big)\Big)`} />
    <p class="tier-p">
      Under <strong>combined slip</strong>, longitudinal and lateral forces interact through
      weighting functions <Math expr={String.raw`G_{x\alpha},\,G_{y\kappa}`} />, which is what bends the
      ellipse. Meanwhile the load on each tyre is set dynamically by acceleration and
      CoG height:
    </p>
    <Math display expr={String.raw`F_{z,\text{front}} = \frac{m g\,b + m\,a_x\,h}{L}, \qquad \Delta F_z = \frac{m\,a_x\,h}{L}`} />
    <p class="tier-p">
      So the &ldquo;friction circle&rdquo; is really a <strong>load- and slip-dependent
      surface</strong> in <Math expr={String.raw`(\kappa,\ \alpha,\ F_z,\ \gamma)`} /> space, changing
      every instant of the corner.
    </p>
    <p class="tier-cite">Refs: Pacejka, <em>Tyre &amp; Vehicle Dynamics</em>; Cossalter, <em>Motorcycle Dynamics</em>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.mathtiers').forEach((root) => {
    root.querySelectorAll('.tier-btn').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const lvl = btn.getAttribute('data-reveal');
        const tier = root.querySelector('.tier-' + lvl);
        if (tier) tier.removeAttribute('hidden');
        btn.setAttribute('hidden', '');
        if (lvl === '2') {
          const b3 = root.querySelector('.btn-3');
          if (b3) b3.removeAttribute('hidden');
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .mathtiers { font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .tier { padding: 0.2rem 0 0.4rem; }
  .tier-p { line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .tier-p strong { color: var(--color-ink); }
  .tier-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.15rem 0;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .tier-tag-1 { color: var(--color-blueprint); }
  .tier-tag-2 { color: var(--color-amber); }
  .tier-tag-3 { color: var(--color-racing); }
  .kept { color: var(--color-ink-faint); text-transform: none; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .tier-cite { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; color: var(--color-ink-faint); margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .tier-btn {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-ink);
    background: var(--color-card);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin: 0.6rem 0;
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    transition: all 0.12s ease;
  }
  .tier-btn:hover { background: var(--color-ink); color: var(--color-paper); }
  .tier-btn.btn-3 { border-color: var(--color-racing); color: var(--color-racing); }
  .tier-btn.btn-3:hover { background: var(--color-racing); color: var(--color-paper); }
  :global(.katex-display) { margin: 0.5rem 0; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; }
</style>
